Constructor
- Can take an optional prop object that contains all the logic for functions within the terminal

init()
- Requires a DOM element as an argument to mount to
- Sets up the event listeners for the terminal (resize, click, keystrokes)

login()
- Writes the login prompt from the props (if exists) and initializes base prompt

writeln() // rename to print? 
- Takes either a string or array with 2 args (string and color), or array of those and writes it to the terminal

input() 
- Returns a promise for input from the user